.SH NAME
rpcrdma_sendctx_get_locked \- Acquire a send context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct rpcrdma_sendctx *" rpcrdma_sendctx_get_locked
.BI "(struct rpcrdma_xprt *r_xprt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "r_xprt" 12
controlling transport instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns pointer to a free send completion context; or NULL if
the queue is empty.

Usage: Called to acquire an SGE array before preparing a Send WR.

The caller serializes calls to this function (per transport), and
provides an effective memory barrier that flushes the new value
of rb_sc_head.
